com.software.reuze

Interface ff_i_MIDIProgramChanges

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    s_SoundCipher, s_SoundCipherScore

    public interface ff_i_MIDIProgramChanges
    An interface storing General MIDI program change constants. These constants can be used to make the code more readable and to relieve the programmer from having to look up the GM specification for program change values.
    The constants are implemented by both the SoundCipher and SCScore classes so they can be accessed using 'dot' notation from instances of any of these classes, for example;
    after: SoundCipher sc = new SoundCipher(this);
    access constants using: sc.FLUTE
    after: SCSCore score = new SCScore();
    access constants using: score.FLUTE

    This class was borrowed from the jMusic library.
    Author:
    Andrew Sorensen, Andrew Brown, Andrew Troedson, Adam Kirby
